overview: The user's intent was to add database functionality, an admin
  dashboard, and authentication to a sleep questionnaire application based on a
  Statement of Work. The agent developed a plan that included updating
  demographic data, creating a Prisma schema for questionnaire responses,
  implementing API routes for data handling, and building a simple admin
  dashboard. A key decision was to simplify the authentication system by
  leveraging Next.js middleware for route protection and a basic cookie-based
  session, which was a refinement from an earlier custom session management
  approach. The agent provided comprehensive instructions for database setup
  using NeonDB and guided the user through testing the implemented features,
  confirming successful questionnaire submission, admin login, and CSV data
  export.
